        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 8:09PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK</headline>
        <description>At 809 PM AKDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers near North
Pole, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
